Afghan Volcano May Hold $82 Billion of Rare-Earth Metals, Times Says

-- B y   C a t h e r i n e   A i r l i e
-- 
2011-09-25T07:01:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-25/afghan-volcano-may-hold-82-billion-rare-earth-metal-times-says.html
An extinct volcano in Afghanistan
may be the site of 53 billion pounds ($82 billion) of rare earth
metals including lanthanum, cerium and neodymium, the  Sunday
Times  reported, citing the  U.S. Geological Survey .  The deposits have been found in rock on the Khanneshin
volcano in the Taliban-controlled areas of Helmand province, the
Times reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Catherine Airlie in London at 
 cairlie@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
 sev@bloomberg.net  